{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b006d827-6d61-4c7f-84a3-5c8f3ae43beb","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine, but I can still walk you through exactly how to identify the runtime and configure dumps.\n\n## 1. Determine CoreCLR vs NativeAOT\n\nRun these checks against your actual PID:\n\n```bash\n# Check if the process loaded libcoreclr.so (CoreCLR indicator)\ncat /proc/<PID>/maps | grep -q libcoreclr && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"Likely NativeAOT\"\n\n# Alternative: check for the coreclr shared library in loaded modules\nls -l /proc/<PID>/map_files/ 2>/dev/null | grep coreclr\n```\n\n**CoreCLR** apps load `libcoreclr.so`. **NativeAOT** apps are self-contained native binaries — no `libcoreclr.so` in the process maps.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configure crash dumps\n\n### For CoreCLR apps\n\nSet these environment variables (e.g. in your systemd unit or shell):\n\n```bash\n# Enable dumps via the CoreCLR runtime\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nType reference: `1` Mini (small, stack only), `2` Heap (managed heap included), `3` Triage (filtered), `4` Full (complete).\n\n### For NativeAOT apps\n\nNativeAOT doesn't use `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump`. Use standard Linux kernel core dumps:\n\n```bash\n# Set core dump pattern (as root)\necho \"/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t\" | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\n# Remove core file size limit for the process\nulimit -c unlimited\n\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\n### For either runtime (systemd services)\n\nIf using systemd, add to your unit file:\n\n```ini\n[Service]\n# For CoreCLR:\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n\n# For NativeAOT (or as a fallback for both):\nLimitCORE=infinity\n```\n\n---\n\n**TL;DR:** Run `grep libcoreclr /proc/<PID>/maps`. If it matches → CoreCLR, use `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump`. If not → NativeAOT, use kernel `core_pattern` + `ulimit -c unlimited`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8cd816ea-15ec-49a1-92fe-0cc5ad71ab20","outputTokens":702,"requestId":"2C46:2DF061:152AF97:17FF983:69F94EFB"},"id":"00a1ac3b-f4d5-4220-9e31-2eda884e33aa","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:59:38.066Z","parentId":"6dfbb2e6-0c6d-4016-bfc5-8ba48f142e7c"}
